{{wikipedia}}

==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[æl|ǣl]], from Germanic ''*ēla-''.  Cognate with Dutch [[aal]], German [[Aal]], Swedish [[ål]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/i:l/}}
*ēl, /<tt>I:l</tt>/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːl|-iːl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any [[fish]] of the order [[Anguilliformes]] which are elongated and resemble [[snake]]s. There are freshwater and marine species.

